Malted Pancakes with Hazelnut Maple Syrup

Syrup:
1 c hazelnut butter
¾ c + 2 tbsp maple syrup
¼ c water
½ tbsp salt

In a small bowl, whisk all of the syrup ingredients together until smooth, then set aside.

Pancakes:
2½ c ap flour
½ c granulated sugar
2 tbsp malted milk powder
2 tbsp baking powder
2 tsp baking soda
2 tsp kosher salt
4 c buttermilk
8 eggs
1 stick unsalted butter, melted
Nonstick cooking spray

In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, malted milk powder, baking powder, baking soda and salt.  In another bowl, whisk the buttermilk and eggs until smooth. Slowly whisk the wet ingredients into the dry until incorporated, then whisk in the melted butter. Make sure not to overmix the batter. Heat nonstick skillet over medium heat. Spray with nonstick cooking spray, then add 1/2 c batter per pancake (depends on size ofpan how many). Let cook until small bubbles appear on the surface and the bottoms are golden brown, 1 1/2-2 min. Carefully flip and let cook until puffed, ~2 min more.

Serve with the hazelnut syrup.
Makes 16 pancakes

Note: nore sure what size you get 16 - makes tons of batter, and very runny - would recommend not putting in all 4c of buttermilk until you see how the batter is
